# pack 
---

Generate javascript files containing all the logic needed to render the question.

By default it generates: 
 * `pie-view.js` - contains all the logic for rendering, includes the individual pies, a pie-player, pie-controller and pie-control-panel. 
 * `pie-controller.js` - contains a map of pie names to their controllers, exports the map to either `window` or `exports`.
 * `pie-configure.js` - contains all the logic for rendering configure elements for a given pie.

You can also generate a single js file `pie-item.js` that defines a custom element with everything pre-defined by adding `--includeComplete | -C`.

### Options

<%= loadFile('common-opts.md') %>
  `--clean` - clean the pie item directory of any pie build assets before running - default `false`
  `--includeComplete` | `-C` - generate a single js file that defines a custom element with everything predefined - default: `false`. This also generates an example markup file `example.html`
  `--addPlayerAndControlPanel` - add the `pie-player` and `pie-control-panel` elements to `pie-view.js` - default: false
  `--app` | `-a` - the app type to use available types are `default` and `catalog`. For now you can just skip this and it'll use the `default` app type.
  `--createArchive` - create an archive from the pie item dir after packing -  default: `false`. 

> The catalog app is used for the `pie-catalog` web app.

### Examples
```shell
pie-cli pack --dir ../path/to/dir
```
